{
  "stem": "15962.7",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So then it was getting more and more difficult to get out of the country.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But as a orphan, the American Joint Distribution offered to pay for my transportation and arrange for taking care of me in Canada.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was unable to get a visa to the United States because the Americans simply did not want to be flooded with immigrants from Europe and had very strict national quotas.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Czech quota was well oversubscribed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had to say goodbye to my hometown, which I was very accustomed to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had many friends in school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And reluctantly [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] went first to England, where I had a cousin, and then by boat to Halifax, Canada, with other refugees.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One of the refugees there was one of the group.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Pavel Kummerman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were-- the last few years, we are looking for him everywhere but couldn't find him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But another boy whom I didn't even know-- we didn't know each other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I had a photograph taken on the ship.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And two years ago, he looked at that photographs and said, that's me, and this is Pavel Kummerman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, you know, 50 years later we found each other again, but not the third one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because Joint.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That-- there was only a-- one could go to Australia or to Canada.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Those were the countries that-- and it turned out, later on, that the reason I could get to Canada is that the Canadians opened a-- were willing to issue visas when the war started to-- to orphans in Central Europe, Jews that were fleeing Hitler.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the powers that were administering the law were very antisemitic in Canada.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
